From Subject Re Shaft drives and Wheelies In article Wayne Orwig writes Is it possible to do a wheelie on a motorcycle with shaft drive No It is imposible due to the shaft The centripital effects of the rotating shaft counteract any tendency for the front wheel to lift off the Well my last two motorcycles have been shaft driven and they will The rear gear does climb the ring gear and lift the rear which gives an odd feel but it still Feeding frenzy Ah 'tis April in and the newbies are bitin' Catch all you want we'll make more Chuck Rogers